  "prompt": "What are some ways to use Moga controllers on a PC?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to use Moga controllers on a PC:\n\n1. Direct Bluetooth Connection\n- Many Moga controllers support Bluetooth pairing directly with Windows PCs\n- Enable Bluetooth on your computer\n- Put the Moga controller in pairing mode\n- Select and pair the controller in Windows Bluetooth settings\n\n2. Moga Smartphone Companion App\n- Download the Moga App for PC\n- This app can help configure and set up the controller\n\n3. Steam Input Support\n- Many Steam games natively support Moga controllers\n- Add the game to Steam and configure controller settings\n\n4. Third-Party Software\n- Use programs like DS4Windows or XOutput\n- These can help map controller inputs and improve compatibility\n\n5. Xbox Controller Emulation\n- Some Moga models can emulate Xbox controllers\n- This provides broader game compatibility\n\n6. Android Emulators\n- If using Android emulators like BlueStacks, Moga controllers often work well\n\n7. Generic USB Connection\n- Some Moga models support direct USB connection to PCs\n- Plug in via micro-USB cable for direct input\n\nNote: Compatibility can vary depending on the specific Moga controller model and the game or software you're using.",
